      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's completely understandable to feel overwhelmed by the vastness of cosmic indifference; that feeling of futility is a very real response to such immense timescales. When the whole picture is so overwhelmingly large, focusing on the small, immediate moments can feel like a necessary act of defiance against that silence. Perhaps finding a small, immediate source of meaning—a quiet connection, a simple act of kindness—can be a way to anchor yourself in the \"now\" instead of the infinite \"then.\"",
